The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Lodha summoned

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, July 20: A criminal complaint has been filed in a local court in Orissa against Rajendra S. Lodha, his two sons, Aditya and Harsh, and another person for alleged forgery and false statement. The complaint has been filed by a shareholder of Mangalam Timber Products of the BK Birla group.

 Admitting the complaint, the sub divisional judicial magistrate of Nawarangpur, has directed Lodha, his sons and Parshotam Lal Vadera to appear before the court on August 17. 

 Lodhas defended themselves saying that the matter was being looked at by the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India (ICAI). 




